		<item>
			<title>Web and Information Technology Accessibility/Consultation Services</title>
			<link>https://legacy.idrc.ocadu.ca/34-services/consultation/396-web-and-information-technology-accessibilityconsultation-services</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://legacy.idrc.ocadu.ca/34-services/consultation/396-web-and-information-technology-accessibilityconsultation-services</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>In addition to working directly with individuals of all abilities, the ATRC works with international organizations that create standards for accessible information design, including the <a href="http://www.mcss.gov.on.ca/mcss/english/pillars/accessibilityOntario">AODA</a>, <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/">W3C</a> and the <a href="http://www.imsglobal.org/accessibility/index.html">IMS Global Learning Consortium</a>.</p>
<p>To support organizations that want to insure that their websites and technologies are meeting the widest possible audience we have a growing number of services.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://websavvy.idrc.ocad.ca/">Web-Savvy</a> (Website accessibility evaluation service)</li>
<li><a href="https://legacy.idrc.ocadu.ca/component/content/?task=view&amp;id=325&amp;Itemid=133">Video Access Media Centre</a></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></description>
